{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b4b67911-ea8d-4f66-b834-10b3ad8c1f56","content":"Your project already has `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` referenced. To use it, run:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts the test runner in **watch mode**. When a test fails, you can edit your source code and **save the file** — the runner will automatically re-execute the tests without a full rebuild, using .NET Hot Reload under the hood.\n\n**Workflow:**\n1. Run `dotnet test --hotreload`\n2. See which tests fail\n3. Edit your code/tests in another terminal or editor\n4. Save — tests re-run automatically\n5. Repeat until green\n\nThis is much faster than running `dotnet test` from scratch each time since it skips the full build cycle.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c77f6266-e6da-403f-80ef-69ee3037afc3","outputTokens":174,"requestId":"7C17:A8FAA:288E2FF:2CF1563:69F94988"},"id":"9d112202-82e4-4036-bb94-cab5c39813b0","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:36:13.955Z","parentId":"6977f74a-ed1d-4788-a9d4-47145c84e7de"}
